STEP 2: NUMERICAL INTEGRATION

Use Trapezoidal Rule to confirm:
∫_0^10▒〖P(t)dt〗

Total Energy = h/42[P(t_0 )+2P(t_1)+2P(t_2 )+⋯+P(t_(n))]
To integrate from 0 to 10, we need power values (P) for all time points (t). Since the Central Difference method only gave us values for t = 2, 4, 6, 8, we calculate the endpoints (t=0 and t=10) using simple forward and backward differences:

P(0) (Forward Difference): (E(2)-E(0))/2=  (1.5-0.0))/2=0.75kW
P(0) (Forward Difference): (E(10)-E(8))/2=  (13.0-9.0))/2=2.0kW
